<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-11T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-11T16:00:00-05:00" n="98" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d98">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/985:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Long</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-11T16:00:00-05:00">December 11, 1941—4
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>526. Reference Department’s circular telegram of December 8, 1 a.m.
                                The Ecuadorean Government asserts willingness to comply, is doing
                                what it can but asks for specific suggestions as to how we exercise
                                preventive power, regulations governing telecommunications were
                                published in the <hi rend="italic">Registro Oficial</hi>, Nos. 478
                                and 479, of July 3 and 4, 1940. The Foreign Minister states that
                                Ecuador will be pleased to modify or amend regulations if we suggest
                                the changes.</p>
                            <p>Axis representatives will probably now use clandestine radio: see our
                                    No.513.<note n="52" xml:id="d98fn1">Dated December 9, 1941,
                                    noon; not printed.</note></p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>